race.comment: MISSILE GIRL (4) continues to race very well, off a let-up here having run on strongly to finish second at Sale last time out in a stronger race. She's had a trial to keep her up to the mark since then and should take plenty of holding out. INTIMEOFNEED (11) presents third up having shown improvement when just edged out at St Arnaud as favourite second up. She should get a nice run on speed and take some catching. EYES WIDE SHUT (13) resumes. She mixed her form last time in but has trialled well leading into this and has a bit of upside. FIVE STAR KING (3) resumes. He doesn't win out of turn but has form in decent races that read well for this. Expect the 4kg claimer to ride aggressively out in front. MONT SAINT MICHEL (8) has been good his past two and has each-way claims.
